Name: pulmonary valve insufficiency
Definition: A pulmonary valve disease that occurs when the pulmonary valve is not strong enough to prevent backflow into the right ventricle. If it is secondary to pulmonary hypertension it is referred to as a Graham Steell murmur.

Name: rheumatic pulmonary valve disease
Definition: A uterine ligament adenocarcinoma that derives_from epithelial cells originating in glandular tissue forming serous lesions.

Name: pulmonary valve stenosis
Definition: An ovarian carcinoma that has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells and derives_from epithelial cells.
Synonym: Ventricular septal defect with pulmonary stenosis or atresia
